          "sentence": "You ___ have told me earlier! I would have helped.",
          "answer": "should",
          "hint": "To express that someone did not do something they were expected to do.",
          "explanation": "'Should have + past participle' expresses regret or criticism about a past action that didn't happen."
        }
      ]
